Normal Solution
O(n^2) time complexity by checking all pairs, which is inefficient for large datasets.
Trie-Based Solution
O(N × 32)

1. Build a binary Trie where each node represents a bit (0 or 1) of the numbers.
2. For each number, traverse the Trie to find the best possible XOR by trying to take the opposite bit at each level (to maximize XOR).

Binary Trie Structure
Instead of:
26 children
Use:
2 children (0 and 1)
Because bits:
0 and 1 are the only possible values for each bit position in a binary representation of numbers.

class Node {
    Node[] child = new Node[2];
}

